<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-276-736  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 276 736.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MIS Week  March 19 1990 v11 n12 p32(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>CBEMA targets information services. (Computer Business EquipmentManufacturers Association)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Depompa, Barbara.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Computer Business Equipment Manufacturers Association (CBEMA)has published 'Information Technology Industry Data Book1960-2000', a report detailing the growth and evolution of thecomputer and telecommunications industries.andP;  CBEMA predictscontinued growth for the information industry, with technologicaladvances, a shortage of office workers, and declining costs allpromoting automation.andP;  Worldwide revenue of the US computer andtelecommunications industry is estimated at $466 billion for 1989,and is expected to reach $1.1 trillion in 2000.andP;  Software andservices is the industry's fastest growing sector, with revenueestimated at $79.6 billion in 1989 and expected to reach $286.62billion by 2000.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Industry AnalysisComputer Business Equipment Manufacturers AssociationProfessional AssociationsCommunications IndustryComputer IndustryReports.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>